      "content": "i get that, but putting them on the same level feels weird. if one side is arguing about what numbers show and the other is just arguing about how they feel about the 2nd amendment, isn't the statistical side objectively more \"correct\" when it comes to whether the laws actually work? isn't the constitutional thing just a separate thing that doesn't change the facts of the crime data?",
