      "content": "The statistical evidence is certainly a measurable fact, but the constitutional argument is not merely a feeling; it is a fundamental legal constraint on government action. The law must operate within the framework of the Constitution, meaning that even if data suggests a perfect solution, an unconstitutional law is invalid. Therefore, the two issues are not separate; the legal framework dictates what *can* be done to affect the crime statistics.",
